article_title: Edward Kosner: Obama the Management Failure
article_text:
President Obama is back in Washington, presumably refreshed after a two-week Hawaiian vacation. Perhaps he'll start 2014 on a vigorous new note that will erase the memory of his lugubrious end-of-the-year news conference and other moments when Mr. Obama looked less like a leader with lousy poll numbers than like a beleaguered manager whose enterprise was failing.

One of the oddities of America's cherished political system is that the job of chief executive of the most powerful operation in the history of the world...

twitter.description: In The Wall Street Journal, Edward Kosner writes that a seasoned executive would have bird-dogged ObamaCare at every stage, from its creation to its rollout.
